OL,3,CMan jailed for killing vulnerable
OL,4,Cuncle in drunken rage
OL,6,FFollowing a hearing at Liverpool Crown
OL,7,FCourt on 20 September, Elms was
OL,8,Fsentenced to 14 years in prison for
OL,9,Fmanslaughter. He will also serve an
OL,10,Fextended four years on licence.
OL,12,FElms told the jury during his evidence
OL,13,Fthat Mr Lavery had accidentally
OL,14,Finjured himself while arguing with Ms
OL,15,FMcKay.
