OL,3,CMan jailed for killing vulnerable
OL,4,Cuncle in drunken rage
OL,6,FJudge Cummings said there were a
OL,7,Fnumber of aggravating factors
OL,8,Fincluding Elms' history of violence,
OL,9,Fthe fact he was under the influence of
OL,10,Falcohol during the time offence, the
OL,11,Ffact Mr Lavery was particularly
OL,12,Fvulnerable and that there was a clear
OL,13,Fabuse of trust.
OL,15,FHe accepted there was some mitigation
OL,16,Fbut said there was little remorse,
OL,17,Fadding: "...you never accepted more
OL,18,Fthan a fraction of your offending and
OL,19,Ftried to lie your way out".
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/8
